AmaZulu King, Goodwill Zwelithini KaBhekuzulu. Rajesh Jantilal/AFP JOHANNESBURG - The late AmaZulu King, Goodwill Zwelithini will be honoured with a Special Official Funeral, category 1. From Saturday, flags will be flown at half-mast at every flag station in the country. READ: EXCLUSIVE: Prince Buthelezi speaks on passing of AmaZulu King The funeral will feature ceremonial elements by the South African National Defence Force. The date has yet to be announced. King Zwelithini passed away on Friday after a long battle with diabetes. He was 72-years old and Africa's longest-reigning monarch. Tributes have been pouring in from all over the world.